python3-opt-roman-numerals (manipulate well-formed Roman numerals)

A library for manipulating well-formed Roman numerals.
Integers between 1 and 3,999 (inclusive) are supported. Numbers beyond this
range will return an OutOfRangeError. The classical system of roman numerals
requires that the same character may not appear more than thrice consecutively,
meaning that 'MMMCMXCIX' (3,999) is the largest well-formed Roman numeral.
The smallest is 'I' (1), as there is no symbol for zero in Roman numerals.
